<li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Henri Bergson, <i>The Creative Mind: An Introduction to Metaphysics</i>, page 163: <i>Strictly speaking they do not constitute multiple states until I have already got beyond them, and turn around to observe their trail. [...] In reality, none of them begins or ends; they all dovetail into one another.</i></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Henri Bergson, Creative Evolution (1911) tr. Arthur Mitchell, Henry Holt and Company</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Henri Bergson, <i>The Creative Mind: An Introduction to Metaphysics</i>, pages 165 to 168.</span></li>
</ol>
